  "text": "The importance of the late endosomal scaffold complex p14-Mp1 for host defense is further emphasized by the increased mortality of the LMCp14 2/2 mice upon Salmonella infection. The high bacterial loads in the liver and spleen of these mice resulted from an uncontrolled replication of Salmonella in p14-deficient macrophages in vivo. Furthermore, the importance of p14 in host defense is also reflected by the inefficient killing of extracellular pathogens by phagocytic cells from patients having reduced p14 protein levels [CITATION_1] .",
